  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">END AIDS portal: Scaling-up HIV and AIDS support services in Zambia through SMS</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">New HIV treatment guidelines in Zambia are not always well understood by people living with HIV or by clinicians, and treatment centres are increasingly understaffed. If the treatment is not taken correctly the HIV virus can become resistant to the drugs and this can ultimately increase the number of AIDS-related deaths. This project uses mobile phones to improve access to information and support about HIV treatment in Lusaka province. It will be possible to send text messages to health agents, and bulk messages will widely disseminate health information. This innovative project will contribute to the goal of reducing the number of new HIV infections to zero.</narrative>
  </description>
